caption.text:
STOP WITH THE MYTHS! Here are 17 common MYTHS:

"Story views don't count as Reel views" Yes, they do! Even if people don’t click on the reel itself

"Long captions get you more views" - Your captions can be long, but they don’t have to be. What matters the most is writing captions that people will actually read

"IG Stories help you grow!" Stories don’t reach new people, so they don’t help you grow

"You shouldn't edit your caption after posting" - This has been disproven in many studies and instagram’s CEO even confirmed that this has no effect

"You should logging off after posting" - Zero data to support this

"Saves are the best for of engagement" - this may haver been true in 2019, but today, SHARES are the best form of engagement

"You need Consistent Aesthetics" - They have little-to-no impact on growth.

"Boosting/Promoting posts hurts your account" - Promoting posts does not impact future engagement. Instagram’s CEO has addressed this numerous times.

"You should remove fake/inactive followers" - This has been shown to lead to a decrease in future reach and engagement

"You should buy followers to boost your account" - Buying likes or followers will KILL your account for the future

"Posting a second time in one day hurts your first post" - There are many factors that determine which post is shown to your followers and in what order. Posting a second time in one day does not hide your first post

"The shadowban is real" - The Shadowban is something that 99% of people will never experience

"Reels should be short and funny" - Reels should be valuable, sharewothy, and captivating

"You need to engage with other accounts for an hour a day!" - Engaging with other accounts can be helpful but is not necessary for growth

"Hashtags are the best way to grow on Insta" - Hashtags are no longer a reliable or effective tool for growing on instagram. Numerous studies have shown their decreased effectiveness

"Reels are the only posts that work. Everything else is a waste" - You can grow with only photos and carousels! Many of the biggest accounts on Instagram NEVER post Reels

caption.text:
¿Quieres saber qué postear en instagram para crecer y facturar? 🤔

 🌟✨ No se pueden perder la entrevista con Brock Johnson, el coach de Instagram, donde nos revela qué tipo de contenido postear en redes sociales para maximizar nuestro crecimiento y engagement. 📈💡

En esta conversación, Brock nos comparte sus mejores estrategias para crear contenido que realmente resuene con nuestra audiencia y nos ayude a construir una marca personal sólida. 🙌🔥

Te invito a chequear @instaclubhub.es para tips sobre  Instagram. 📊🔍

¡No se pierdan esta entrevista llena de tips valiosos para llevar su perfil al siguiente nivel! 🚀✨

#InstagramGrowth #SocialMediaTips #BrockJohnson #CarolinaMillan #InstaHub #ContentCreation #BrandBuilding #InstagramStrategy

caption.text:
The 4-4-3 Rule ⤵️

Your bio is like a billboard!

Most people are only glancing at your profile before they follow you (or not).

4️⃣ Lines in the bio — if you add more than 4 lines to the bio, instagram will cut it off with a “…more” button.

This means that a potential follower will have to do extra steps just to read your bio! ❌

Instead, be concise and direct! 4 lines or less!

4️⃣ Story Highlights — the chances that someone scrolls through a long list of highlights is low, so make sure your first 4 highlights are the most important!

I recommend the following:
• Start Here
• About Me
• (what you do/what you sell)
• Testimonials/examples/before-and-afters

3️⃣ Pinned posts — most people pick their “most viewed” post to be their pinned post, but that not always what’s best!

Instead, I recommend that your pinned posts be:
1. Start here/self-introduction
2. Lead magnet/promotion
3. Exemplary post/what people can expect

If you made it this far, make sure you don’t forget to Like this post! I’m testing to see if y’all still enjoy reading my longer captions, so I’ll use the “likes” on this post as an indicator (:
